      "@type": "fabio:Section",
      "dcterms:title": "Introduction",
      "fabio:hasContent": "Non-progressive cerebellar ataxias (NPCAs) manifest in infancy with abnormal gross motor development and hypotonia, followed by the appearance of ataxia. Dysarthria, intellectual disability and spasticity are often present. Only seven genes have been described for autosomal recessive NPCA..."
